# descriptive regression model - FEMALES
descr_lm_f <- lm(eq5d ~  as.factor(age) * imd + as.factor(year),hse_combined[hse_combined$sex =="Female",], weights = wt)
# descriptive regression model - ALES
descr_lm_m <- lm(eq5d ~  as.factor(age) * imd + as.factor(year),hse_combined[hse_combined$sex =="Male",], weights = wt)

# predict means by strata
# QUESTION: WHICH YEAR SHOULD WE USE TO PREDICT MEANS?
# OR BETTER USE EMPIRICAL AGGREGATE MEANS?
imd_lvls <- levels(hse_combined$imd)
pred_df_f <- pred_df_m <- data.frame(age = rep(16:90,5),imd = rep(imd_lvls,each = 75), year = 2010)

Inequality

MOST DEPRIVED / LEAST DEPRIVED RATIO

I couldnt figure out how to construct SE from coef ratios analytically, so I just ran 1,000 bootstrap iterations and computed empirical means (pooling all years together).

takes a while to run…..

# rel eq5d inequality most depr. / least depr. ratio

# define bootstrap function
ineq_boot1 <-  function(hse_combined, sex = "Female",boot_iter = 1000, print_i = F){
  # takes the hse_combined data set and samples from it boot_iter-times
  # then takes the ratio of the mean eq5d by age for imd 5 and imd 1
  # slow and inefficient procedure
  
  # mean
  rel_ineq_f <- aggregate(eq5d ~ age+imd,hse_combined[
    hse_combined$sex ==sex & 
      hse_combined$imd %in% levels(hse_combined$imd)[c(1,5)],
    ],
    mean)
  rel_ineq_f <- reshape(rel_ineq_f,idvar = "age",timevar = "imd", direction = "wide")
  rel_ineq_f <- cbind(age = rel_ineq_f$age, mean = rel_ineq_f[,3]/rel_ineq_f[,2])
  
  # sparse df
  min_f_df <- hse_combined[
    hse_combined$sex == sex & 
      hse_combined$imd %in% levels(hse_combined$imd)[c(1,5)],
    c("age","imd","eq5d")
    ]
  
  # boot loop
  boot_f <- data.frame(age = 16:90) 
  for(i in 1:boot_iter){
    if(print_i){
       print(i)
    }
    temp_df_f <- min_f_df[sample(1:nrow(min_f_df),nrow(min_f_df),replace = T),]
    means_i <- aggregate(eq5d ~ imd + age,temp_df_f,mean)
    means_i <- reshape(means_i,idvar = "age",timevar = "imd", direction = "wide")
    mean_ineq_i <- cbind(age = means_i$age, means_i[,3]/means_i[,2])
    boot_f <- merge(boot_f,mean_ineq_i,"age",all.x = T,suffixes = c(paste0(i,"x"),paste0(i,"y")))
  }
  
  ineq_95ci_f <- apply(boot_f[,-1],1,function(x) quantile(x,c(0.025,0.975),na.rm = T))
  ineq_95ci_f <- t(ineq_95ci_f)
  colnames(ineq_95ci_f) <- c("l95","u95")
  ineq_df_f <- cbind(age = boot_f$age,mean = rel_ineq_f[,2],ineq_95ci_f)
  
  
  tbl <- kableExtra::kable(
    ineq_df_f,
    format = "html",
    col.names = c("age","Mean ineq ratio","lower 95%CI","Upper 95%CI"),
    digits = 2,
    ) %>%
      kable_styling(full_width = F)
  
  # ....
  ineq_df_f <- data.frame(ineq_df_f)
  plot_df <- ineq_df_f
  p1 <- ggplot(ineq_df_f) +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 1, size = 0.5) +
    geom_ribbon(aes(x = age, ymin = l95, ymax = u95, col = sex ), fill = "pink",alpha = 0.3 ) +
    geom_line(aes(x=age,y=mean, col = sex),col ="red", size = 1.5) +
    theme_minimal()
  
  res <- list(
    "tbl" = tbl, 
    "p1" = p1,
    "plot_df" = plot_df
    )
  
  return(res)
}

pre/post 2010 - F test

eq5d = age x imd x post_2010 (males only for now)

# post 2010 dummy
hse_combined$post_2010 <- hse_combined$year >= 2010

# pre/post 2010 INTERACTION model - MALES
post_2010_lm_m <- lm(eq5d ~  as.factor(age) * imd * post_2010,
                 hse_combined[hse_combined$sex =="Male",], 
                 weights = wt)

# same model without post_2010
non_post_2010_lm_m <- lm(eq5d ~  as.factor(age) * imd,
                 hse_combined[hse_combined$sex =="Male",], 
                 weights = wt)

# test of difference in F statistics between both model
anova(post_2010_lm_m,non_post_2010_lm_m)
# ==> it's highly signficant - interpretation unclear
